                        <h2>hybrid seed</h2>
                        <p>
                              "In agriculture and gardening, hybrid seed is produced by deliberately cross-pollinated plants which are genetically diverse. Hybrid seed is common in industrial agriculture and home gardening. It is one of the main contributors to the dramatic rise in agricultural output during the last half of the 20th century.[1] Alternatives to hybridization include open pollination and clonal propagation."
